annotations: The astral plane

The astral plane is a plane of existence postulated by classical, medieval, oriental, and esoteric philosophies and mystery religions. It is the world of the celestial spheres, crossed by the soul in its astral body on the way to being born and after death, and is generally believed to be populated by angels, spirits or other immaterial beings.
The ascended masters

In Theosophy, the ascended masters are spiritually enlightened beings who in past incarnations were ordinary humans, but who have undergone a series of spiritual transformations originally called initiations.
She went on for a while about our president
By the time of the “Phenomenal Nature” exhibition at the Met and the writing of the song, Jenkins can only be referring to Donald Trump’s term as the 45th President of the United States
I ran into Perry at Lowell’s place

The official lyric is “I ran into Peri at Lola’s place” (the vinyl has a lyric sheet if one needs a reference). Peri is psychic and astrologer Peri Lyons https://www.instagram.com/perilyons/?hl=en. Lola is actress and songwriter Lola Kirke https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lola_Kirke
Saint Germain

Comte de Saint Germain was an 18th century philosopher, adventurer, composer, alchemist, and general bon vivant. Omung his eccentricities were his refusal to tell anyone his birth name and his insistence that he was over 500 years old. Relevant to the bookkeeper, Saint Germain is said to be the Wisdom Master of the Seventh Ray (the Freedom of God) according to the Summit Lighthouse. https://www.summitlighthouse.org/saint-germain/
Inn of the Seventh Ray

A fancy restaurant and inn in Topanga, CA, in the mountains near Malibu. The menu specializes in local and organic foods, and bills itself as “Los Angeles’ Most Romantic Restaurant.” The Seventh Ray refers to a concept from several religions, most recently in the 20th century as an element of New Age metaphysical healing methods such as Reiki.

Phenomenal nature
 She said, ”Sculpture is not just formed from penetration
 You see, men have lost touch with the feminine”

Referring to Mrinalini Mukherjee’s exhibition at the Metropolitan Museum of Art, Phenomenal Nature. Mukhergee was an Indian sculptor who worked extensively with fiber, ceramic and bronze in her 40-year career. The security guard is right – while much traditional sculpture is an act of violent penetration (chisel into stone), this artist’s medium is softer, additive, and modern.

description.plain:
Cassandra says of the track: “Michelangelo is a song about being in limbo. It’s the first song I wrote for the album & it never had a chorus that feels fitting, because the song never really arrives at any grand conclusion. It’s a bardo, and there’s so much rich information in that in-between space, if we can stand to take a good hard look.

I’m looking at trauma, and wondering just how baked it is into my DNA. I’m exploring my relationship to past experiences, and asking how much control I have over falling into, or even perpetuating and calcifying, established roles. I’m simultaneously licking the wounds of a phantom limb and learning how to walk again.

It’s a metaphor that falls apart as soon as you watch an actual 3-legged dog in action; everything in their physiology adjusts from imbalance to a new orientation– their gate changes, they learn to redistribute their weight, and they go on running, fetching, panting, living, and finding their balance. It’s so human, on the other hand, to complicate the healing process by pushing against our experience."

Source

annotations:
I wanna be the blank white screen
 Allow the movies to be seen

‘An Overview On Phenomenonal Nature’ is an album of stories and an album about stories. Jenkins believes that everyone has something to say.

Here on the first track she is telling her audience that she wants to be a voice and a storyteller not just for herself but for others.

On another track on the album – ‘Hard Drive’ – Jenkins sings about experiences she’s had with a security, a bookkeeper and one of her friends. All these people have their own stories and Jenkins is telling a tiny part of them, acting as the “blank screen” for their characters to come to life.

I’m Michelangelo
 And I carve myself out of marble
 When I don’t know how to grow
 Flowers out of arrows

As both the artist and the medium, she is wholly responsible for crafting the direction and shape that her life takes – as we all are.
Arrows represent the many adversities that life may throw our way; taking the shape of tragic events, personal struggles, etc. By not knowing how to grow flowers out of arrows, she is confessing the difficulty she has in taking such struggles and turning them around into something beautiful, productive, or learned.

In 2019, Cassandra Jenkins was supposed to go on tour with Purple Mountains. Before the tour started, David Berman died of suicide.

Soon after Berman died, Jenkins realized she had forgotten to cancel a flight to Norway that she had planned before agreeing to go on tour. When she noticed it was set to depart at the exact time her first Purple Mountains show was meant to start, she took it as a sign and went on the trip.

Source: https://pitchfork.com/features/rising/cassandra-jenkins-an-overview-on-phenomenal-nature-interview/

body.plain: Cassandra was supposed to join David Berman (known as the man behind Silver Jews) on his comeback tour as Purple Mountains back in 2019 but just before the tour even started David Berman commited suicide taking the music world by surprise.

annotations: Landing in Oslo

Jenkins has revealed that before singing to tour with the Purple Mountains, she had a scheduled trip to Norway.

Forgetting the trip, the singer later used it as a way to try to make sense of her grief over David Berman’s suicide.
Farewell Purple Mountains

Purple Mountains was an American indie rock project formed by musician and poet David Berman.

Jenkins was supposed to tour, opening for the band, in 2019. Berman’s suicide in August of the same year dissolved the group.
I’m on a 787

Interstate 787 (I-787) is an auxiliary Interstate Highway in the US state of New York. I-787 is the main highway for those traveling into and out of downtown Albany.

It relates to Jenkins learning how to drive in “Hard Drive”.
